subject: Birthday Bookings SO# 9352
body:
Thank you for booking your birthday with us! I have attached our digital invitation templates.

Weâ€™re excited to help make this celebration unforgettable! Below are the details and important information related to your event:

Package Reminders:

The total guest count includes all attendees (adults and children aged 2 and up).
You can add on up to 5 additional guests to your package. Any additional guests over 5 will upgrade your party package to the next size up.
IMPORTANT - Changes to your party package:

20 - 40 person party packages: Adjustments to the number of attendees can be made on the day of your event. However, we can not upgrade a 40-person to a 50-person package within 7 days
of your party date as a 50-person package requires two hosts.
50-person package : Changes can only be made up to 7 days before your party. You will be unable to downgrade your 50-person package within 7 days of your party date. This is because 50-person
packages require two hosts to accommodate all 50 guests.

Party Itinerary:
9:45 - 10:00AM: Bring party supplies (immediate family only)

10:00 - 11:00AM: Food, cake, & celebrations

11:00 - 11:30AM: Interactive show

11:30 - 11:45AM: Clearing room out

Party guests have general admission to enjoy zoo.

Set up : Immediate family may enter party room 15-minutes before your time slot to set up
Tear down : Immediate family has 15-minutes after your 90-minutes to bring supplies out.

Additional 30-Minutes: $75.00.
Please let us know in advance if you would like to add additional time to your party. We can not guarantee the day of your party that we can accommodate additional time.

Food Reminders:

Youâ€™re welcome to bring your own food and drinks, however they must be nut-free & alcohol-free.
If you plan to cut a cake, please bring your own cake-cutting knife.
Please be aware that we do not have a freezer.

Party Supplies:
We provide paper supplies
as part of our standard party setup:

Cups
Plates
Napkins
Cutlery
Table Paper

Bringing Your Own Supplies:

If you prefer to bring your own supplies , youâ€™re welcome to do so. Should you wish for our host to set up using your
party supplies , please ensure they are brought in prior to your event date and notify us in advance.
Please note : Our host will only set up the typical supplies listed aboveâ€”plates, napkins, cups, cutlery, and tablecloths. Any additional decorations outside of these items (unless
purchased through Reptilia) will not be set up by our host.

Important Decoration Restrictions
We ask that you do NOT bring:

Confetti, glitter, or sequins
Wall decorations (e.g., banners)
Electric hot plates or other burning hazards
Pinatas

Balloons in the zoo or playground (balloons must remain in party rooms)

While we do allow balloons in our party rooms, they must not enter the zoo or playground. Balloons can find their way into our animal exhibits and cause harm to our animals. Balloons
can return to your car after your party is finished. Balloons must not be filled with anything besides helium or air.

Important Deadlines to Remember:

Party Details Confirmation : Please confirm all party details
7 business days prior to the event
Pizza Orders : All pizza orders must be confirmed
before the Wednesday prior to your party
Room Size Changes : Requests for room changes within 7 business days of your party are not guaranteed.

Punctuality & Cancellation Policies

Punctuality : Please ensure all guests arrive on time, as we cannot extend the scheduled room time on the day of your event.
Cancellation :

Within 7 days of booking: No refund will be issued
Within 15 days of booking: 50% of the amount paid will be refunded
30+ days prior to booking: Full refund

Drop-Off Parties
For parties where parents are dropping off children and not staying for the event:
Please ensure that all children are picked up at the front at the designated time.

Additional Notes:
Your party host greatly appreciates tips!

Weâ€™re here to make this celebration stress-free and fun for you and your guests! If you have any questions
or require assistance leading up to your event, please donâ€™t hesitate to contact us.

We look forward to celebrating with you soon!

Sincerely,

Lauren Webber

Booking Coordinator

Business: 905.761.6223

Address: 2501 Rutherford Road, Concord, ON

Email:
bookings.vaughan@reptilia.org

My working hours may not be your working hours. Please do not feel obligated to reply outside of your normal work schedule.

subject: Reminder: UPDATE: Home For The Holidays
body:
Email from Youth Without Shelter
Thank You For Supporting Our Youth  
Hello jane,

As we step into the New Year, we are sending our warmest wishes to you for health, happiness, and many moments of joy ahead. On behalf of our residents and staff, thank you for being such an essential part of the YWS family.

Because of you, our shelter truly felt like home this holiday season. Long-time and first-time supporters came together in the most beautiful way. Volunteers showed up with generous donations, helped us sort gift-in-kind items, cooked comforting meals, wrapped presents, and filled our space with care and kindness.

Thanks to your incredible generosity, we were also thrilled to reach our $600,000 goal for the Home for the Holidays Double Match Campaign , making it our most successful holiday campaign to date . This extraordinary milestone will have a lasting impact on the youth we serve and ensure critical programs and supports remain available when they are needed most.

Because of you, our youth were able to enjoy a calm and joyful holiday, something that can be especially hard during this time of year. They opened personalized gifts paired with heartfelt cards of encouragement, shared laughter over games, and enjoyed delicious meals made with love.

The magic did not stop there. The Home Depot team transformed our shelter into a festive wonderland, complete with decorations and a glowing light-up arch at the stairs that made the space feel straight out of a movie scene.
﻿
Thank you for keeping our youth in your hearts and for standing with us every step of the way. Your generosity, time, and compassion make everything we do possible, and we are deeply grateful to have you as part of our community as we head into the year ahead.

Monika Fox
YWS Director of Philanthropy

Looking to volunteer or donate goods ?
Please reach out to Varagi at 416-748-0110 x 62 or at  varagi@yws.on.ca .

Etobicoke, ON

subject: UPDATE: Home For The Holidays
body:
Email from Youth Without Shelter
Thank You For Supporting Our Youth  
Hello jane,

As we step into the New Year, we are sending our warmest wishes to you for health, happiness, and many moments of joy ahead. On behalf of our residents and staff, thank you for being such an essential part of the YWS family.

Because of you, our shelter truly felt like home this holiday season. Long-time and first-time supporters came together in the most beautiful way. Volunteers showed up with generous donations, helped us sort gift-in-kind items, cooked comforting meals, wrapped presents, and filled our space with care and kindness.

Thanks to your incredible generosity, we were also thrilled to reach our $600,000 goal for the Home for the Holidays Double Match Campaign , making it our most successful holiday campaign to date . This extraordinary milestone will have a lasting impact on the youth we serve and ensure critical programs and supports remain available when they are needed most.

Because of you, our youth were able to enjoy a calm and joyful holiday, something that can be especially hard during this time of year. They opened personalized gifts paired with heartfelt cards of encouragement, shared laughter over games, and enjoyed delicious meals made with love.

The magic did not stop there. The Home Depot team transformed our shelter into a festive wonderland, complete with decorations and a glowing light-up arch at the stairs that made the space feel straight out of a movie scene.
﻿
Thank you for keeping our youth in your hearts and for standing with us every step of the way. Your generosity, time, and compassion make everything we do possible, and we are deeply grateful to have you as part of our community as we head into the year ahead.

Monika Fox
YWS Director of Philanthropy

body:
Email from Youth Without Shelter
Thank You For Supporting Our Youth  
Hello jane,

This holiday season, our hearts are full of gratitude for you, our incredible donors, volunteers, and supporters. Through our Home for the Holidays campaign , your generosity took many meaningful forms, from financial gifts and essential items to lovingly prepared meals that helped YWS truly feel like home when it mattered most.

Thanks to you, we are so close to our goal. Just $28,500 remains to reach our $300,000 Home for the Holidays target , which will be matched thanks to our generous benefactors.
DOUBLE YOUR IMPACT
There is still time to make a difference in 2025.
Your donation helps provide safe shelter, nourishing meals, and life-changing support for youth on their journey toward stability, healing, and hope, while also ensuring you receive a 2025 charitable tax receipt for gifts made on or before December 31, 2025.

We truly could not make YWS a home without you. Thank you for standing with us, believing in our youth, and being part of their journey.
﻿
Wishing you and yours a joyful holiday season and a happy, hopeful New Year.

subject: Re: [ChifferCo/chiffer] [NetSuite] Support Legacy Taxing System (Issue #19782)
body:
tahasub left a comment (ChifferCo/chiffer#19782)
I'm not sure if setting isTaxable to true at the line-item level might break saving invoices for this org or others. Even though CodeSignal uses Legacy tax, it looks like NetSuite ignores this option when Per-Line Taxes on Transactions is enabled. So I think itâ€™s safer to keep this set to false and let NetSuite decide how and where taxes should be calculated.
Since everything works well for this org and others, I'd keep it as is for now unless we run into a case that needs it. Wdyt?
